    <h2>The Challenge</h2>
    <p>Methanex Corporation, the world's largest producer and supplier of methanol, operates manufacturing facilities across multiple continents. Managing the integrity of equipment exposed to methanol production environments, which include high temperatures, corrosive catalysts, and pressurized synthesis gas, demands rigorous data management and systematic corrosion monitoring.</p>
    <p>Methanex's integrity data had accumulated over decades in various formats and systems. Thickness measurement records existed in proprietary vendor databases, engineering assessments in standalone documents, and inspection photographs in unlinked file systems. This fragmentation made it difficult to perform comprehensive corrosion trend analysis and slowed the engineering team's ability to respond to integrity questions from operations and management.</p>

    <h2>The Solution</h2>
    <p>Methanex implemented <strong>Visions Enterprise</strong> as the centralized platform for all integrity data across its operations. The implementation prioritized data consolidation, migrating historical thickness measurements, inspection records, and equipment metadata from legacy systems into a single unified database.</p>
    <p>Corrosion circuits were systematically defined and validated against process flow diagrams and field conditions. Automated corrosion rate calculations replaced manual spreadsheet analyses, providing consistent, up-to-date remaining life estimates for all monitored circuits.</p>

    <h2>The Results</h2>
    <p>The data consolidation effort delivered immediate and ongoing benefits:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Engineering analysis time reduced by 45%</strong> by eliminating manual data gathering and consolidation from multiple sources.</li>
      <li><strong>Identified 12 previously unrecognized high-corrosion-rate circuits</strong> during the data migration process, enabling proactive mitigation before any failures occurred.</li>
      <li><strong>Standardized corrosion rate methodology</strong> across all facilities, enabling meaningful cross-site benchmarking for the first time.</li>
      <li><strong>Improved turnaround planning accuracy</strong>, with data-driven scope development reducing unnecessary inspection by 22% while increasing coverage of high-risk circuits.</li>
    </ul>
    <blockquote>The most surprising outcome was discovering integrity risks that had been hiding in our data all along. Consolidating everything into one platform made patterns visible that we simply could not see before.</blockquote>

    <h2>Expanding the Program</h2>
    <p>Building on the success of the initial data consolidation, Methanex is now implementing risk-based inspection across its global operations using the Visions Enterprise platform. The high-quality, consolidated data established during the initial phase provides the foundation for accurate RBI assessments, accelerating the transition from time-based to risk-based inspection planning across the entire equipment population.</p>
    <p>The Methanex experience underscores a critical lesson: data quality and consolidation are prerequisites for advanced integrity management capabilities. Organizations that invest in getting the data foundation right position themselves for compounding returns as they layer on RBI, predictive analytics, and other advanced capabilities.</p>
